pkg-config
------------------------------------------
pkg-config is a script to make putting together all the build
flags when compiling/linking a lot easier.

To use pkg-config, do something like the following in your configure.ac

    PKG_CHECK_MODULES([GNOME], [gtk > 1.2.8 gnomeui >= 1.2.0])

This puts the neccesary include flags to compile/link something against
libgnomeui and all its dependencies in $(GNOME_CFLAGS), and the -L/-l flags
for linking in $(GNOME_LIBS).

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.24-2
  glib2-2.14.4-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  cygwin-1.5.24-2
  autoconf2.5-2.61-1
  automake1.7-1.7.9-3
  binutils-20060817-1
  cygport-0.3.7-1
  gawk-3.1.5-4
  gcc-core-3.4.4-3
  libtool1.5-1.5.23a-2
  make-3.81-1
  pkg-config-0.21-1
  sed-4.1.5-2

Canonical website:
  http://pkg-config.freedesktop.org/wiki/

Canonical download:
  http://pkgconfig.freedesktop.org/releases/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack pkg-config-0.22-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./pkg-config-0.22-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/pkg-config-0.22-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/pkg-config-0.22-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

  /usr/bin/pkg-config.exe
  /usr/share/aclocal/pkg.m4
  /usr/share/doc/pkg-config-0.22/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/pkg-config-0.22/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/pkg-config-0.22/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/pkg-config-0.22/INSTALL
  /usr/share/doc/pkg-config-0.22/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/pkg-config-0.22/README
  /usr/share/man/man1/pkg-config.1.gz

